<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-colorgroup.xml">ColorGroup</db:link> type is used to define a set of colors with certain roles. Although a <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-colorgroup.xml">ColorGroup</db:link> has no visual appearance, it defines colors used to customize rendered items.</db:para>
<db:para>Default values of colors are equal to active group colors of default-constructed <db:code>QPalette</db:code>.</db:para>
<db:para>The following code can be used to create a color group with some colors specified:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">ColorGroup {
    alternateBase: &quot;red&quot;
    base: &quot;green&quot;
}
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-palette.xml">Palette</db:link> type exposes color groups for each QML item state.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
